This lemma is important because it confirms that the coercion map `↑` from `upperHalfPlaneSet` to `ℂ` is surjective onto the upper half-plane set `ℍ₀`. This is needed to ensure that the differentiability results hold for functions defined on `ℂ` but restricted to `ℍ₀`.

